ail unit of hess corp for  billion following the closure of the acquisition in late  all hess gas stations will be rebranded as speedway gas stations by the end of  the transaction completed the transformation of hess into an energy company focused solely on exploration and production effectively reversing the amerada merger almost  years prior environmental recordedit the new york times reported on october   that a barge with a load of  barrels  m of kerosene struck a reef in the hudson river spilling  us gallons  m of fuel immediately hess assumed responsibility for the cleanup the coast guard worked alongside the red star company to clean and to contain the spill to one area coast guard official mr holmes said the weather and wind conditions are almost as close to perfect as they could get and this contributed to a quicker and surer cleanup than could otherwise be according to the new york times mr holmes also said that  percent of the spill would be gone in three days due to the natural evaporation rate of kerosene even though most kerosene evaporates toxic chemicals such as benzene stay in the water and harm certain fish hess claims that their corporate policy has long stressed their fundamental commitment to comply with applicable environment health and safety laws and regulations and they claim to clean every spill made in accordance with a new york state department of environmental conservation dec agreement the hess corporation will pay  million in fines and also bring  gasoline stations and oil storage facilities into compliance with state requirements the agreement addresses more than  violations at  gas stations and hesss brooklyn major oil storage facility the agreement is aimed at resolving hesss violations in the decs new york city and lower hudson valley regions in a recent water contamination case against several major us oil companies the hess corporation will pay part of a  million settlement the case was filed by  public water providers in  states against the oil companies over drinking water contamination caused by the gasoline additive methyl tertiary butyl ether mtbe the settlement also stipulates that the settling parties pay their share of treatment costs of the plaintiffs wells that may become contaminated or require treatment for the next  years in regard to greenhouse gas emissions hess outlined in their  corporate sustainability report a four element strategy to reduce and control emissions the strategys steps include monitoring measuring managing and mitigating through reporting results energy efficiency and recovery and carbon capture and trading the company intends to improve its environmental impact locationsedit prior to the march   announcement of its withdrawal from refining and retail sales of petroleum products hess operated gas stations in alabama arkansas california connecticut delaware district of columbia florida georgia indonesia maryland massachusetts new hampshire new jersey new york north carolina pennsylvania rhode island south carolina tennessee and virginia in may  speedway llc a subsidiary of marathon petroleum company announced they would purchase hess corporations retail business for  billion hess had  locations along the eastern united states the conversion from hess branding to speedway branding took place over the course of  toy trucksedit the hess toy trucks helicopters police cars airplanes space shuttles and rescue vehicles have been popular christmas gift traditions for  years  in the us it is one of the longest running toy brands on the us market since  hess gas stations have sold toy trucks each year around christmas time each year the model changes to a new design older models are considered collectibles and typically sell for a few hundred or even thousands of dollars for example the  truck sells for about – depending on condition hess periodically has a rare truck such as the  chrome truck with helicopter and the  chrome mini which were given away at a stockholder meeting and more recently the  truck given to new york stock exchange employees to commemorate its name change from amerada hess corporation to hess corporation in christmas of  the hess corporation donated  of its  hess toy trucks and race cars to the salvation army for the underprivileged children in north dakota there was also a hess toy truck float in the annual macys thanksgiving day parade in new york that participated from  up to  when the hess corporation was sold the toy truck business continued after the sale of hess retail unit to speedway modelsedit the  version of the hess toy truck there have been several instances in which nontruck vehicles were sold under the hess toy truck bannerunreliable source  tanker ship based on the hess voyager  patrol car  helicopter with motorcycle and cruiser  suv with motorcycles notethis marks the th anniversary of the hess toy truck  race car with racer  helicopter and rescue the trucks since  are  first hess truck  red firetruck  truck with barrels  truck with racer note starting in  mini toys were made with the full size trucks  white firetruck note similar to the  hess firetruck  tanker truck  truck with racer  truck with racer  patrol car note this is the first toy car made by hess  rescue truck note this marks the th anniversary of the hess toy truck  truck with helicopter  emergency truck  truck with racers  rec van with motorcycle and sand buggy  space shuttle transport  firetruck  helicopter with motorcycle and cruiser  truck with airplane  truck with race cars  suv with motorcycles note this marks the th anniversary of the hess toy truck  emergency truck with rescue vehicle  helicopter transport  monster truck with motorcycles  truck with front end loader  race car and racer  jet transporter  truck with race car  helicopter and rescue  truck with tractor  th anniversary tanker truck  miniature  hess truck tanker replica note this was a limited production run and was only sold through the hess toy truck website