das financing of the recently completed tender offer hess planned to cancel the shares and the cost of the acquisition would be absorbed by the newly formed company one shareholder at the meeting quipped it looks to me as if hess is buying amerada with ameradas money proponents of the deal won and the us billion merger combining a purely production company with a refinery and marketer operation was completed however controversy was not yet extinguished by the stockholder confirmation a class action federal lawsuit in  claiming the proxy vote information was misleading in  a court agreed that the company falsely claimed to have considered each companys assets as a reason for the merger a former hess station in rensselaer county new york in february  hess acquired the  shares of the meadville corporation it didnt already own and rebranded all  merit gas stations as hess the merit gas station chain were primarily in the boston new york and philadelphia markets in  amerada hess purchased triton energy limited in a cash tender deal valued at approximately us billion triton one of the largest independent oil and natural gas exploration and production companies in the us had earned a reputation as a maverick oil company due to its highly successful yet potentially risky overseas exploration according to amerada hess press releases at the time tritons major oil and gas assets in west africa latin america and southeast asia would strengthen its exploration and production business and give it access to long life international reserves hess also stated that the purchase was expected to immediately increase the companys perday barrel output by more than  percent also in  amerada hess entered into a joint venture with at williams oil co of winstonsalem north carolina the company and its gas stations were called wilcohess eventually there were  wilcohess stations following on the heels of the triton purchase energy prices fell and global economies weakened amerada hess struggled through the following years posting a us million loss in  due primarily to a us million charge relating to its writedown of the ceiba oil field but then posting steadily increasing profits from  through  when the company posted us billion in net income in may  amerada hess corp changed its name to hess corp on january   the company announced that it would close the hovensa refinery in st croix united states virgin islands by midfebruary  the refinery will then serve as a storage terminal hess will permanently close its port reading new jersey petroleum refinery by the end of february  gas prices rose to their highest levels since october and hess said it will lay off  of  employees exit the refinery business and seek a buyer for its  storage terminals it will focus on exploration and production a hess press release announces the companys plans for fully exiting the companys downstream businesses including retail energy marketing and energy trading  there is no link between the rise in gas prices after the announcement of the closing of the woodbridge port reading nj facility the output of that facility was more geared to the aviation and specialty fuels markets and not automotive grade products on march   hess announced that it would sell its domestic refineries and retail operations and that it would also sell its holdings in indonesia and thailand the new york times also reported that hess retail and refinery operations contributed about  percent of the companys revenue it also noted that hess will sell its holdings in indonesia and thailand the company will focus exclusively on oil production following a recent trend in the oil industry for companies to spin off their downstream assets and focus on their more profitable upstream business conocophillips and marathon oil have also made similar spinoffs in recent years with phillips  and marathon petroleum respectively in april  hess corp announced it would be selling its russian unit to lukoil for  billion in july  hess corp said it would sell its energy marketing unit to uk firm centrica for around  billion hess corp announced in october  that it was planning on selling its east coast and stlucia storage terminal network to buckeye partners lp for  million hess corp announced in december  that it is selling its indonesian assets to an indonesian petroleum consortium on january   hess filed for a tax free spinoff of its gas station network the newly formed company was to be known as hess retail and will include over  stores throughout the eastern united states before completing the spinoff marathon petroleum subsidiary speedway llc announced on may   that it would acquire the retail unit of hess corp for  billion following the closure of the acquisition in late  all hess gas stations will be rebranded as speedway gas stations by the end of  the transaction completed the transformation of hess into an energy company focused solely on exploration and production effectively reversing the amerada merger almost  years prior environmental recordedit the new york times reported on october   that a barge with a load of  barrels  m of kerosene struck a reef in the hudson river spilling  us gallons  m of fuel immediately hess assumed responsibility for the cleanup the coast guard worked alongside the red star company to clean and to contain the spill to one area coast guard official mr holmes said the weather and wind conditions are almost as close to perfect as they could get and this contributed to a quicker and surer cleanup than could otherwise be according to the new york times mr holmes also said that  percent of the spill would be gone in three days due to the natural evaporation rate of kerosene even though most kerosene evaporates toxic chemicals such as benzene stay in the water and harm certain fish hess claims that their corporate policy has long stressed their fundamental commitment to comply with applicable environment health and safety laws and regulations and they claim to clean every spill made in accordance with a new york state department of environmental conservation dec agreement the hess corporation will pay  million in fines and also bring  gasoline stations and oil storage facilities into compliance with state requirements the agreement addresses more than  violations at  gas stations and hesss brooklyn major oil storage facility the agreement is aimed at resolving hesss violations in the decs new york city and lower hudson valley regions in a recent water contamination case against several major us oil companies the hess corporation will pay part of a  million settlement the case was filed by  public water providers in  states against the oil companies over drinking water contamination caused by the gasoline additive methyl tertiary butyl ether mtbe the settlement also stipulates that the settling parties pay their share of treatment costs of the plaintiffs wells that may become contaminated or require treatment for the next  years in regard to greenhouse gas emissions hess outlined in their  corporate sustainability report a four element strategy to reduce and control emissions the strategys steps include monitoring measuring managing and mitigating through reporting results energy efficiency and recovery and carbon capture and trading the company intends to improve its environmental impact locationsedit prior to the march   announcement of its withdrawal from refining and retail sales of petroleum products hess operated gas stations in alabama arkansas california connecticut delaware district of columbia florida georgia indonesia maryland massachusetts new hampshire new jersey new york north carolina pennsylvania rhode island south carolina tennessee and virginia in may  speedway llc a subsidiary of marathon petroleum company announced they would purchase hess corporations retail business for  billion hess had  locations along the eastern united states the conversion from hess branding to speedway branding took place over the course of  toy trucksedit the hess toy trucks helicopters police cars airplanes space shuttles and rescue vehicles have been popular christmas gift traditions for  years  in the us it is one of the longest running toy brands on the us market since  hess gas stations have sold toy trucks each year around christmas time each year the model changes to a new design older models are considered collectibles and typically sell for a few hundred or even thousands of dollars for example the  truck sells for about – depending on condition hess periodically has a rare truck such as the  chrome truck with helicopter and the  chrome mini which were given away at a stockholder meeting and more recently the  truck given to new york stock exchange employees to commemorate its name change from amerada hess corporation to hess corporation in christmas of  the hess corporation donated  of its  hess toy trucks and race cars to the salvation army for the underprivileged children in north dakota there was also a hess toy truck float in the annual macys thanksgiving day parade in new york that participated from  up to  when the hess corporation was sold the toy truck business continued after the sale of hess retail unit to speedway modelsedit the  version of the hess toy truck there have been several instances in which nontruck vehicles were sold under the hess toy truck bannerunreliable source  tanker ship based on the hess voyager  patrol car  helicopter with motorcycle and cruiser  suv with motorcycles notethis marks the th anniversary of the hess toy truck  race car with racer  helicopter and rescue the trucks since  are  first hess truck  red firetruck  truck with barrels  truck with racer note starting in  mini toys were made with the full size trucks  white firetruck note similar to the  hess firetruck  tanker truck  truck with racer  truck with racer  patrol car note this is the first toy car made by hess  rescue truck note this marks the th anniversary of the hess toy truc